    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe following config will produce the following error message \r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.opt.list = true\r\nvim.opt.listchars = {\r\n    tab = \"▸\", -- tab requires a string of two characters, unlike other listchars options\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nFailed loading config.options\r\n\r\nvim/_options.lua:0: E474: Invalid argument\r\n\r\n# stacktrace:\r\n  - vim/_options.lua:0 _in_ **_set**\r\n  - vim/_options.lua:0 _in_ **__newindex**\r\n  - nvim-lazyvim/lua/config/options.lua:120   # This is the listchars tab assignment\r\n  - /LazyVim/lua/lazyvim/config/init.lua:228\r\n  - /LazyVim/lua/lazyvim/config/init.lua:227 _in_ **_load**\r\n  - /LazyVim/lua/lazyvim/config/init.lua:236 _in_ **load**\r\n  - /LazyVim/lua/lazyvim/config/init.lua:267 _in_ **init**\r\n  - /LazyVim/lua/lazyvim/plugins/init.lua:11\r\n  - nvim-lazyvim/lua/config/lazy.lua:9\r\n  - nvim-lazyvim/init.lua:2\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis error is actually meant to indicate that tab requires 2 or 3 characters, and a single character representation for it is invalid. (I'm not sure why this is the case, but it seems to be).\r\n\r\nI used [this](https://www.reddit.com/r/neovim/comments/10qepmg/i_cannot_set_listchars/) to guide me to setting my options like this, which can be loaded without error.\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.opt.list = true\r\nvim.opt.listchars = {\r\n    eol = \"¬\",\r\n    tab = \"▸ \", -- tab requires a string of two characters\r\n    extends = \"»\",\r\n    precedes = \"«\",\r\n    trail = \"·\",\r\n    space = \"·\",\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nCan we add a better error message here? Or allow single-character `listchars` options for `tab`?",
    "closed_at": null,
